A drug that costs $2.40 a day can reduce the risk of a heart attack.
Thousands of heart attack patients are getting access to a drug that costs around €2.40 a day, when authorities recommended it be given to more people and for longer-term use.
The anticoagulation medicine ticagrelor reduces the risk of new heart attacks in patients with heart disease.
The medicine is already being given 12 months after a heart attack, which reduces the risk of having a stroke or another heart attack.
