The charm of vinyl: who buys records?
Lonely, middle-aged men love vinyl.
Before you can post your angry protest in the comments section, under the name of NotAllLonelyMiddle-aged Men, this claim is based on actual research data.
According to the research company YouGov, the reason behind the much-discussed re-emergence of vinyl records is not the millennial generation’s boom, when millennials want to feel a physical object in their hands, but instead the underlying nostalgia of middle age.
