According to the newspaper, in both cases, a person was walking in the dark on the motorway and the court ruled that motorists could not expect to run into a pedestrian on the motorway in the middle of the night.
Last year, a police officer was acquitted of charges of manslaughter after she ran into a man lying on the A1 motorway near Paynerne one night in August 2014.
The court heard that the 22-year-old victim had ingested a lot of alcohol and passed out on the road.
The court ruled that the driving behaviour of the police – who were responding to the emergency call – was justified and that the man lying on the road was a “completely exceptional and unforeseen situation”.
